00:02:28.009 --> 00:02:30.009
That's architectural.

00:02:30.009 --> 00:02:33.009
That's construction.

00:02:33.009 --> 00:02:37.009
Why the change in illustrations?

00:02:37.009 --> 00:02:42.009
The building analogy highlights a specific point.

00:02:42.009 --> 00:02:50.009
The illustration of the farmer doesn't focus on the farmer's impact on the growth of a plant.

00:02:50.009 --> 00:02:54.009
In that illustration, the farmer waters the seedling.

00:02:54.009 --> 00:02:59.009
But it's God that makes the plant grow.

00:02:59.009 --> 00:03:07.009
However, the illustration of building or construction focuses on the builder's involvement

00:03:07.009 --> 00:03:10.009
or the Bible teachers involvement.

00:03:10.009 --> 00:03:17.009
The one constructing a building has considerable influence or the quality of the end product.

00:03:17.009 --> 00:03:21.009
What kind of materials does he select?

00:03:21.009 --> 00:03:24.009
Is he thorough in his work?

00:03:24.009 --> 00:03:28.009
Or does he cut corners to get the job done faster?

00:03:28.009 --> 00:03:31.009
Or with less effort?

00:03:31.009 --> 00:03:37.009
Now let's read the 10th verse of First Corinthians chapter 3.

00:03:37.009 --> 00:03:42.610
According to the undeserved kindness of God that was given to me,

00:03:42.610 --> 00:03:49.610
I laid a foundation as a skilled master builder, but someone else is building on it.

00:03:49.610 --> 00:03:55.610
But let each one keep watching how he is building on it.

00:03:55.610 --> 00:04:03.610
