00:04:09.610 --> 00:04:12.610
But what was that foundation?

00:04:12.610 --> 00:04:14.610
Verse 11 says,

00:04:14.610 --> 00:04:23.610
For no one can lay any other foundation than what is laid which is Jesus Christ.

00:04:23.610 --> 00:04:30.610
Paul had helped establish the congregation there in Corinth based on the teachings of Jesus,

00:04:30.610 --> 00:04:33.610
the foundation of the truth.

00:04:33.610 --> 00:04:43.610
Building on that foundation, others would become Bible teachers and help still others to progress toward baptism.

00:04:43.610 --> 00:04:50.610
That is why Paul cautioned in verse 10 to keep watching how we build.

00:04:50.610 --> 00:04:53.610
We can affect the outcome.

00:04:53.610 --> 00:05:00.610
So to all of us Bible teachers, including parents, we ask the question,

00:05:00.610 --> 00:05:05.949
how are we building on the foundation?

00:05:05.949 --> 00:05:08.949
Why does it really matter?

00:05:08.949 --> 00:05:12.949
Let's read verses 12 and 13.

00:05:12.949 --> 00:05:21.949
