00:06:38.949 --> 00:06:45.949
An official report indicated that over 5,000 students died.

00:06:45.949 --> 00:06:48.949
Think about it.

00:06:48.949 --> 00:06:54.949
Prior to the earthquake, schools were in session and everything seemed fine.

00:06:54.949 --> 00:07:00.949
Students and faculty were coming and going on a daily basis.

00:07:00.949 --> 00:07:14.230
But the unforeseen earthquake proved that the building methods used were not of the quality needed to prevent collapse and terrible carnage.

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:29.230
First Corinthians 313 makes clear that how we build spiritually when teaching Bible students or our children is just as important.

00:07:29.230 --> 00:07:38.230
Now, notice the sobering point made in verses 14 and 15.

00:07:38.230 --> 00:07:46.800
If anyone's work that he has built on it remains, he will receive a reward.

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:51.800
If anyone's work is burned up, he will suffer loss.

00:07:51.800 --> 00:07:58.800
